    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThere is no bell sound from the terminal emulator. However, `:!echo <CTRL+G>` (or `:!echo \"\\a\"` for nushell) and other triggers like hitting Esc in normal mode do trigger a bell.\n\nAccording to [the documentation](https://neovim.io/doc/user/options.html#'belloff'), this should not be the case.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean`\n2. `:set bo=`\n3. `:terminal`\n4. `echo <CTRL+G>` (or `echo \"\\a\"` for nushell)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nA bell sound\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.2, 0.11.0-dev-1709+ga9cdf76e3a\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, vim doesn't have a built-in terminal emulator\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 10\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nCould reproduce with cmd, powershell and nushell\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nNone\n\n### Installation\n\nFrom (precompiled) binary version",
