        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Is there a win 10 version later than \"1809\" that we should bump `:help supported-platforms` to?\n\n<img height=\"100\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/64e776c6-350c-4f91-8c6e-89a9c45198a9\" />\n\nSure, for example, [Windows Terminal](https://github.com/microsoft/terminal?tab=readme-ov-file#installing-and-running-windows-terminal) requires Windows 10 2004 or later (this repo contains the source code of `conhost.exe`).\nI verified this issue on 22H2 last week, and I can also test 1903 / 1909 / 2004 etc. :)\nref: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windows_10_version_history",
            "created_at": "2026-04-05T16:12:28Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/32367#issuecomment-4189125618",
            "id": 4189125618,
